    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Structural Benchmarks ",
        "text_level": 1,
        "page_idx": 58
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "24. Prior Actions are specified in Table 2 of the MEFP ",
        "page_idx": 58
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Submit the 2020 budget to the National Assembly for approval in line with the program parameter. ",
        "page_idx": 58
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Based on the conclusion of the audit of BCC and CBT, adopt restructuring and funding plans for CBT and BCC in coordination with the BEAC, COBAC and IMF staff. ",
        "page_idx": 58
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Complete audit of remaining domestic arrears. Coverage of the audit should include at least i) all remaining ÔÇ£Grand Travaux PresidentielsÔÇØ and ii) all potential arrears not yet reviewed from the Infrastructure ministry. ",
        "page_idx": 58
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "25. Structural benchmarks are specified in Table 2 of the MEFP. Outstanding SBs are governed by the previous TMU. ",
        "page_idx": 58
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Publication of a quarterly note on the oil sector, in line with the template agreed with the IMF staff, including detailed information on debt service to Glencore, quarterly, starting endDecember 2019 (Table 2). The note issued at end-December will cover developments up to the end of the previous quarter (June 2019). ",
        "page_idx": 58
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "i. The note will comment on the recent development in the oil sector, including information related to production, export, and new exploration over the previous quarter, and expectation and forecast for the next 6 months. ",
        "page_idx": 58
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "ii. The note will also provide a detailed account of the flow of oil revenue. Oil revenue will be reported by categories and the corresponding types of payments, in-cash (payment made in cash by oil companies) and in-kind (payment made in crude oil by oil companies). Other information will include information on the sale of government-owned crude oils, such as gross sales revenue, volume sold, transaction prices, operating costs (ÔÇ£Cash-callÔÇØ) to oil ",
        "page_idx": 58
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "companies, transportation cost, interest payments, principal repayment, other related fees paid to service the Glencore loan and the final amount of sales revenue accrued to the Treasury. ",
        "page_idx": 59
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "In consultation with IMF staff, adopt a clearance strategy of domestic arrears based on the completed results of both audits by end-December 2019. ",
        "page_idx": 59
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The clearance strategy should include transparent and objective factors for prioritization, including economic and social impact, and the effect payment is expected to have on the banking sector. It should address clearance modalities, notably whether and how much the government will pay in cash, restructure and securitize. ",
        "page_idx": 59
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The strategy should also indicate the plan to finance clearance. ",
        "page_idx": 59
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Complete the implementation of the recommendations of the audit of the 47 exemption conventions with a view to removing or modifying those that do not comply with the legal texts or that have not been correctly executed, by end-February 2020. ",
        "page_idx": 59
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Publication every six months of a list of all new, renewed or extended tax and customs exemptions during the previous six months. The first list should be published at end-January and should cover the period July to December 2019. ",
        "page_idx": 59
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Sign performance contracts with the management of CBT and BCC, by end March 2020. ",
        "page_idx": 59
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Allocate new resources (building and software) to tax directorates in charge of large and medium firms in with line FAD's recommendations, by end April 2020. ",
        "page_idx": 59
    },
